threads.com:
Greetings, /c/itizens!

Just wanted to go over a couple of guidelines for posting on /c/ if you are new here and a friendly reminder for those who aren't.

Try to avoid making single-image requests. Making a single image thread deletes a previous thread from the last page. Please include 4 to 5 similar images in your thread to get it going. Use resources like danbooru, gelbooru or even Google Image Search.

Check the catalog to avoid making a duplicate thread. This way, we can share and contribute more images more effectively and efficiently.

If bumping a thread, please include a picture instead of just writing 'bump' and please do not necrobump threads that have reached their image limit. This restricts the diversity and natural flow of the board. Threads are meant to come and go and sometimes they are even better the next time around.

Finally, as much as /a/ is a discussion board, /c/ is a board for sharing images. Please respect the threads of other users and they will do the same to yours as well!

Today feels like an extra special day for giving thanks, and showing gratitude! What better way to give thanks and show gratitude to Homura Akemi than a brand new thread?

Taking a moment every day to feel gratitude is an excellent habit to build. To appreciate something is to give it your attention, and consideration - far too often, the nice items, nice places, and nice people that make our lives so wonderful slip into our periphery, and out of our focus. Seemingly dull things we’ve grown accustomed to can glimmer brilliantly with new life once they catch the limelight of our attention.

May your attention go today (and tomorrow, and even the day after that) where it has gone before, so the sparkle of your eye can be shared with the everyday loves of your life again.

I hope you’ll join me in giving the best magical girl ever some of your precious attention and time, here in Thread 132.

My short story will basically cover what a normal day in this universe looks like for her whenever I'm not around.
